url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pcm-dpc/COVID-19/master/dati-andamento-nazionale/dpc-covid19-ita-andamento-nazionale.csv"
COVID19IT <- read.csv(file = url, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
# View(COVID19IT)

# create data for analysis
data = data.frame(date = as.Date(COVID19IT$data),
                  infected = COVID19IT$totale_casi)
data$x = as.numeric(data$date) - min(as.numeric(data$date)) + 1

DT::datatable(data)

Nonlinear grow models

Exponential growth model

\[ \mu(x) = \theta_1 \exp\{\theta_2 x\} \] where \(\theta_1\) is the value at the origin (i.e. \(\mu(x=0)\)), and \(\theta_2\) represents the (constant) relative ratio of change (i.e. \(\frac{d\mu(x)}{dx }\frac{1}{\mu(x)} = \theta_2\)). Thus, the model describes an increasing (exponential growth if \(\theta_2 > 0\)) or decreasing (exponential decay if \(\theta_2 < 0\)) trend with constant relative rate.

mod1_start = lm(log(infected) ~ x, data = data)
start = list(th1 = log(coef(mod1_start)[1]), 
             th2 = coef(mod1_start)[2])
mod1 = nls(infected ~ th1 * exp(th2 * x), data = data, start = start)
summary(mod1)

Logistic growth model

\[ \mu(x) = \frac{\theta_1}{1+\exp\{(\theta_2 - x)/\theta_3\}} \] where \(\theta_1\) is the horizontal asymptote, \(\theta_2\) represents the x-value at the inflection point of the curve, and \(\theta_3\) represents a scale parameter.

mod2 = nls(infected ~ SSlogis(x, Asym, xmid, scal), data = data)
summary(mod2)
##

Gompertz growth model

\[ \mu(x) = \theta_1 \exp\{-\theta_2 \theta_3^x\} \] where \(\theta_1\) is the horizontal asymptote, \(\theta_2\) represents the value of the function at \(x = 0\) (displacement along the x-axis), and \(\theta_3\) represents a scale parameter.

The difference between the logistic and Gompertz functions is that the latter is not symmetric around the inflection point.

mod3 = nls(infected ~ SSgompertz(x, Asym, b2, b3), data = data)
summary(mod3)
## 
## Formula: infected ~ SSgompertz(x, Asym, b2, b3)

Models comparison

models = list("Exponential model" = mod1, 
              "Logistic model" = mod2, 
              "Gompertz model" = mod3)
tab = data.frame(loglik = sapply(models, logLik),
                 df = sapply(models, function(m) attr(logLik(m), "df")),
                 Rsquare = sapply(models, function(m) 
                                  cor(data$infected, fitted(m))^2),
                 AIC = sapply(models, AIC),
                 BIC = sapply(models, BIC))
knitr::kable(tab)
loglik df Rsquare AIC BIC
Exponential model -87.32008 3 0.9971155 180.6402 182.5573
Logistic model -85.05721 4 0.9977179 178.1144 180.6706
Gompertz model -82.92615 4 0.9982653 173.8523 176.4085 
ggplot(data, aes(x = date, y = infected)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(y = fitted(mod1), color = "Exponential")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = fitted(mod2), color = "Logistic")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = fitted(mod3), color = "Gompertz")) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Infected", color = "Model") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Exponential" = "red3", 
                                "Logistic" = "dodgerblue3",
                                "Gompertz" = "green4")) +
  scale_y_continuous(minor_breaks = seq(0, coef(mod2)[1], by = 1000)) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "2 day", date_labels =  "%b%d",
               minor_breaks = "1 day") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

Predictions

Point estimates

df = data.frame(x = seq(min(data$x), max(data$x)+14))
df = cbind(df, date = as.Date(df$x, origin = data$date[1]-1),
               fit1 = predict(mod1, newdata = df),
               fit2 = predict(mod2, newdata = df),
               fit3 = predict(mod3, newdata = df))
ggplot(data, aes(x = date, y = infected)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit1, color = "Exponential")) +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit2, color = "Logistic")) +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit3, color = "Gompertz")) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, coef(mod2)[1])) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Infected", color = "Model") +
  scale_y_continuous(minor_breaks = seq(0, coef(mod2)[1], by = 1000)) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "2 day", date_labels =  "%b%d",
               minor_breaks = "1 day") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Exponential" = "red3", 
                                "Logistic" = "dodgerblue3",
                                "Gompertz" = "green4")) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "top",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=60, hjust=1))

Prediction intervals

library(investr)
pred1 = cbind(df, predFit(mod1, newdata = df, interval = c("prediction"), level = 0.95))
pred2 = cbind(df, predFit(mod2, newdata = df, interval = c("prediction"), level = 0.95))
# pred3 = cbind(df, predFit(mod3, newdata = df, interval = c("prediction"), level = 0.95))
# :-(( error 
pred3 = cbind(df, lwr = df$fit3, upr = df$fit3)
ggplot(data, aes(x = date, y = infected)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit1, color = "Exponential")) +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit2, color = "Logistic")) +
  geom_line(data = df, aes(x = date, y = fit3, color = "Gompertz")) +
  geom_ribbon(data = pred1, aes(x = date, ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), 
              inherit.aes = FALSE,
              fill = "red3", alpha=0.3) +
  geom_ribbon(data = pred2, aes(x = date, ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), 
              inherit.aes = FALSE,
              fill = "dodgerblue3", alpha=0.3) +
  geom_ribbon(data = pred3, aes(x = date, ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), 
              inherit.aes = FALSE,
              fill = "green4", alpha=0.3) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, max(pred2$upr))) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Infected", color = "Model") +
  scale_y_continuous(minor_breaks = seq(0, max(pred2$upr), by = 1000)) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "2 day", date_labels =  "%b%d",
               minor_breaks = "1 day") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Exponential" = "red3", 
                                "Logistic" = "dodgerblue3",
                                "Gompertz" = "green4")) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "top",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=60, hjust=1))
